==English==

===Noun===
'''pirate''' (plural: [[pirates]])

# One who [[plunder]]s at sea; commonly attacking merchant vessels, though often [[pillage|pillaging]] port towns.
# {{internet}} One who reproduces [[copyright]]ed works without [[permission]] for the purpose of [[distributing]] them to others for free
# {{internet}} One who downloads copyrighted works from the internet illegally.

===Etymology===
'''pirate''' used to be writen with a 'y', hence it comes from the (?) word [[pyrate]], wich loosely translates as 'men of fire' or 'fire-persons' (see [[-ate]]), because of the [[pyr]] "fire", related to English [[pyre]] (via Latin [[pyra]]) and fire via [[PIE]].

